Add the Input Widget to Formula Queries

Retrieving values from the input widget to use in a formula can be done through the UI. You can add the input widget as a column in a query or with SAQL.

Steps to add the input widget to a calculation:

* Use the input widget to build a formula in a new or existing query.
* Add an input widget to your dashboard, create a query or select an existing one for building your formula, edit the query and add a column selecting Input.
* Search and select an input query, then add another column and select Formula, use the formula editor to create a calculation using values from the input query.

Steps to add the input widget to a SAQL Query:

* Add an input widget to your dashboard, create a query or select an existing one for building your formula, edit the query in Query Mode.
* Position your cursor where you want to add values from the input query and click the Add Input link.
title: Adding Input Widget to Formula Queries in CRM Analytics
